fields.label: Par.1.1.1
fields.html: Each priest takes a metal pot, and they go to the well. The chief priest draws water from the well. Thrice, he pours the water on the floor. Then, the water he draws serves to fill the metal pot hold by the assistant priest. Thrice, the chief priest pours a little bit of water in the second metal pot, the assistant priest pours the water on the ground. Then, he draws water to fill the second metal pot. Once, it is filled, he draws water to fill his metal pot. They go back to the ritual area with the metal pots filled.

fields.label: Par.1.2.1
fields.html: Both metal pots are put on the ritual table. The chief priest sits crossed legged on the seat. Then, he takes one metal pot and pours water in a jug to clean it before pouring the water on the floor. He repeats this action thrice, and then fills the jug with water. Then, he pours some water from the jug to another jug three times, each time pouring the water on the ground afterwards. He repeats this with a second jug. When the three jugs are cleaned, he fills them with water from the metal pot. The chief priest gives the metal pot to the assistant priest, who pours some water in the water container. The chief priest circles his right hand within the water container, then pours the water on the ground. The assistant priest pours some water in the water container, the chief priest holds the water container and moves it in order to make circle the water within it, then he pours the water on the ground. This operation is repeated twice. The chief priest puts the water container on his base, and the assistant priest pours water in it. Each priest takes a metal pot, and they go to the well.

fields.label: Par.1.3.1
fields.html: The chief priest draws water from the well. He fills the metal pot hold by the assistant priest. Once, it is filled, he draws water to fill his metal pot. They go back to the ritual area with the metal pots filled.

fields.label: Par.1.4.1
fields.html: Both priests, one after the other, fills the water container with the water contained in the respective metal pots. Each priest keeps his metal pot, and they go to the well.

fields.label: Par.1.5.1
fields.html: The chief priest draws water from the well. He fills the metal pot hold by the assistant priest. Once, it is filled, he draws water to fill his metal pot. They go back to the ritual area with the metal pots filled.

fields.label: Par.1.6.1
fields.html: Both priests, one after the other, fills the water container with the water contained in the respective metal pots. Each priest keeps his metal pot, and they go to the well.

fields.label: Par.1.7.1
fields.html: The chief priest draws water from the well. He fills the metal pot hold by the assistant priest. Once, it is filled, he draws water to fill his metal pot. They go back to the ritual area with the metal pots filled.

fields.label: Par.1.8.1
fields.html: The chief priest puts his metal pot on the ritual table, while the assistant priest puts it near the window. The chief priest gives a vaselike jug to the assistant priest, who puts it near the window next to the metal pot. The chief priest sits crossed legged on the seat. Then, he takes a vaselike jug in his right hand and implements in his left hand. He cleans the implements one after another by pouring water on them, and then puts them in the water container. When all the implements are in the water container, the chief priest cleans his left hand by pouring water on it from the vaselike jug that he still holds in his right hand. Eventually remain on the ritual table one metal pot and two vaselike jugs.

fields.label: Par.2.1.1
fields.html: The chief priest stands up, puts his sandals on, and goes outside the ritual area. The assistant priest takes the vaselike jug near the window and goes outside the ritual area.

fields.html:

fields.label: Par.2.2.1
fields.html: First getting a nanny-goat which gives milk into the ritual precinct, making the other purifier priest hold her near him, and making her stand facing the Eastern direction, washing her teats (of the udder), makes (them) clean. The milk taker priest, holding a jug that has been made pure in the left hand, comes near to that nanny-goat and sitting on her left side facing the Southern direction, reciting three times. Making his right hand pure three times, he makes pure one teat of the nanny-goat.

fields.label: Par.2.3.1
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

ašəm aša.sara vacaŋha
ašəm aša.sara šiiaoϑana

fields.label: Par.2.7.1
fields.html: Reciting this much, the milk taker priest sits again, and while reciting ašǝm, squirts milk for the first time on the floor. While reciting aša.sara manaŋha, he squirts milk into the jug. While reciting ašǝm, he squirts milk on the floor for the second time. While reciting aša.sara vacaŋha, he squirts milk into the jug for the second time. While reciting ašǝm, he squirts milk on the floor for the third time. While reciting aša.sara šiiaoϑana, he squirts milk into the jug for the third time.

fields.label: Par.2.8.1
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm (2×)

fields.label: Par.2.8.1

fields.label: Par.2.10.1
fields.html: Reciting this much, caressing the nanny-goat’s back, first, he recites one time aloud. The second time, he recites once in a low tone.

fields.label: Par.2.11.1
fields.html: Then taking that milk jug into the ritual precinct, he puts (it) in the stone niche.

fields.label: Par.3.1.1

fields.label: Par.3.1.2

fields.label: Par.4.1.1
fields.html: The assitant priest stands up. He takes the vaselike jug in his left hand and the knife in his right hand. He pours water on the knife in order to clean it.

fields.label: Par.4.2.1

xšnaoϑra ahurahe mazdā̊

fields.label: Par.4.2.1
fields.html: As informed in the ritual of bringing the barsam, taking the purified jug in the left hand and the knife in the right hand, he goes to the date palm tree, and cleans one of its leaves with the right hand, then reciting three times. Making the right hand along with the knife pure three times, he makes the date palm leaf pure.

fields.label: Par.4.3.1
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm

fields.label: Par.4.3.1
fields.html: Cutting off its top edge with the knife, he throws it down, and cutting the leaf from the stem, making it pure once again, keeping it in the jug, he brings it to the ritual precinct.

fields.label: Par.4.6.1
fields.html: Of the pomegranate tree from which the twig is to be taken, removing a stalk of that tree, first cleaning (it), he comes (back), and as written above, taking in the left hand the jug which has been made pure and a knife with a metal handle in the right hand, he goes in front of that tree and reciting three times. Making the right hand along with the knife pure three times, he makes the stalk of that tree pure.

fields.label: Par.4.6.1
fields.html: With his right hand, he touches the pomegranate twig four times and after each time he pours water on his right hand. Then, while reciting, he touches with his right hand the pomegranate twig and cleans his right hand.

fields.label: Par.4.7.1
fields.html: Cutting a little of its upper portion with the knife, he throws it down, and as much of the stalk as is required, cutting off that much from the stem, making it pure once again.

xšnaoϑra ahurahe mazdā̊

fields.label: Par.4.9.1
fields.html: He puts the pomegranate twig within the vaselike jug.

fields.label: Par.4.10.1
fields.html: Taking it in the right hand, he comes into the ritual precinct.

fields.label: Par.4.10.2
fields.html: He puts the pomegranate twig also in the pure cup (in which) the date-palm leaf is kept, or alternately putting (it) in another pure cup, he puts (it) in the stone niche also.

fields.label: Par.4.10.3
fields.html: He puts the knife and the vaselike jug on the ritual table.

fields.label: Par.4.10.4
fields.html: The assistant priest sits crossed legged, and the chief priest takes the vaselike jug and the knife in order to put the vaselike jug on the floor outside the pāvi and the knife next to the window.

fields.label: Par.5.13.1
fields.html: In that, he pours water three times vertically and three times horizontally on the table in such a way that it gets purified all around.

fields.label: Par.5.14.1
fields.html: After that removes all the implements to arrange on the table. Among them, first removing the pair of moon-shaped stands, he arranges (them) at the front (of the table) in the Eastern direction towards the chief priest’s left hand. Then removing the mortar, he puts (it) on the edge towards the fire on the chief priest’s right hand side. Then removing 5 cups, out of which he puts inverted 2 libation cups near the front on the chief priest’s right side. And he puts 1 cup for the ring with bull’s hair near that. He puts 1 cup near the base of the moon-shaped stand towards the fire. And he puts 1 cup filled with water on the chief priest’s left side on the edge (of the table) towards the fire. After that removing 5 saucers, from which he puts 1 saucer for the milk inverted on the base of the moon-shaped stands. He places a second saucer in between the mortar and the cup of the bull’s hair (ring), for putting the hom and the pomegranate twigs (into them). He partially covers a third saucer on that cup filled with water, which is towards the fire on the chief priest’s left side. If the bull’s hair (ring) is required to be covered, then he places 1 saucer near the cup in which the bull’s hair ring is kept, and if the bull’s hair (ring) is not required to be covered, then it is not kept; and he puts 1 saucer for keeping the consecrated bread midway on the edge (of the table) towards the fire. Then removing the knife, he puts it near to himself at the centre (of the table). Then removing the bundle, he puts it near the knife and finally he puts the bull’s hair ring in the cup meant for it. The perforated saucer and the pestle are left in the water container itself. And counting the bundle wires, he makes sure that (the number) is accurate, i.e. if the Yasna is to be performed, then counting 23 wires correctly, keeps them on the table, the remaining that are left, those he puts back into the water container.

fields.label: Par.6.1.1
fields.html: Holding one wire for preparing the libation in the left hand, he puts the left hand along with the wire on the two cups for preparing the libation which are lying inverted near the front on the table, and taking the bull’s hair ring from its cup in the right hand.

fields.label: Par.6.2.1
fields.html: Purifying (the bull’s hair ring) in the water of the container one thousand times, he recalls mentally the 101 names of God, and after making it pure, he puts (it) back in its cup.

fields.label: Par.6.3.1
fields.html: Then taking the libation wire in the right hand, striking the (two) libation cups (on the table) with both hands, he makes (them) upright. And putting the libation wire on the cups, he holds them in the pinch of both hands, and reciting the Avestan (text), takes the bāj.

fields.label: Par.6.7.1
fields.html: Saying the above ašǝm word, taking both the libation cups within the water container, touches the surface of water (with them).

fields.label: Par.6.8.1

fields.label: Par.6.8.1
fields.html: While reciting the above words, he keeps circling both cups on the water surface. While reciting yazatanąm, he keeps holding both cups still on the water. While reciting ϑβā, he circles the cups on the water again. While reciting ašaonąm, he partially fills both the cups with water. While reciting kuxšnīša, he fills out the cups with water completely. While reciting us.bī.barāmi, he holds up both cups above the water (surface) without touching (it). While reciting raϑβasca bǝrǝzatō, he puts both the cups on the rim of the water container. And while reciting gāϑā̊sca srāuuaiiōit, bringing both the cups over the table, he puts (them) again at their place.

fields.label: Par.6.9.1
fields.html: Reciting this Avestan (text), releases the bāj. While reciting, the libation maker (priest), holding the cup near to him in the right hand, puts upright with the left hand the milk saucer, which is lying inverted on the base of the moon-shaped stands, on the second libation cup which is towards the fire, and pouring into it two driblets from the libation cup in the right hand.

fields.label: Par.6.10.2
fields.html: Reciting tauua ahurāne ahurahe again one time in a low tone, he puts the libation wire on the libation cup.

fields.label: Par.7.1.1
fields.html: After taking the date-palm leaf from that pure cup, in which the date-palm leaf and the pomegranate twig have been kept, he puts (it) on the moon-shaped stands and puts the pomegranate twig on the base of the moon-shaped stands. And then from the barsam wires, if a Yasna is to be performed, then after counting accurately twenty-two wires, he holds (them) in the left hand.

fields.html: After removing the bundle outside again, while reciting two Ahuna Vairiia, he ties two front knots, similar to (tying) the girdle, to the date-palm leaf with the right hand.

fields.label: Par.7.15.1
fields.html: And then while reciting the two Ahuna Vairiia for releasing the bāj, taking the knife in the right hand, he cleans by cutting the edges above the ends of the date-palm leaf, which have been tied in two knots.

fields.label: Par.7.16.1
fields.html: He recites one time again in a low tone. Then, he puts the bundle on the moon-shaped stands with both hands and taking out one wire from the bundle, he puts (it) on the base of the moon-shaped stands towards the milk saucer, and (puts) the libation wire in the hand back on the libation cup.

xšnaoϑra ahurahe mazdā̊

fields.label: Par.8.1.1
fields.html: The libation maker priest, losing the purity of his right hand, wipes (and) cleans (it), then he holds, in the pinch of the right hand, five or seven pieces of hom twigs, which have been taken out from the box (and) kept in the metal vessel, and removing one saucer with the left hand, reciting three times. Turning the hom twigs three times in the pinch of (his) hand, he makes the hand pure upto the wrist.

fields.label: Par.10.35.1

fields.label: Par.10.36.1

fields.label: Par.10.36.1
fields.html: While reciting the above aϑā zī nǝ̄ humāiiō.tara aŋhǝn words, he holds the pestle in the right hand and holding the hom and pomegranate twigs from inside the mortar in the pinch of the right hand, while reciting aϑā, he touches the bundle; while reciting zī nǝ̄, he touches the milk saucer; while reciting humāiiō, he touches the hom cup kept near the base of the moon-shaped stands; while reciting -tara, he touches the table; and while reciting aŋhǝn, he puts the hom and pomegranate twigs back into the mortar.

fields.label: Par.10.37.1
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm

fields.label: Par.10.37.1
fields.html: And then holding the libation cup in the left hand and the pestle in the right hand, he recites four Ahuna Vairiia. And beginning the first of the four Ahuna Vairiia (yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā). While reciting these words, he pours one driblet of libation with the left hand into the mortar from the libation cup and putting back the cup, with the right hand he pounds the hom (and) pomegranate twigs using the pestle. And from ratuš upto that vāstārǝm, he completes the entire Ahuna Vairiia, until there he rings the mortar. (After) completing the first Ahuna Vairiia, holding the pestle in the left hand, he holds (it) above the perforated saucer and picking up the mortar with the right hand, he pours one driblet of hom on the lower surface of the pestle in such a way that it drops via the pestle through the perforated saucer into the cup below.

fields.label: Par.10.37.2
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm

fields.label: Par.10.37.2
fields.html: And beginning the second Ahuna Vairiia (yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašāt). While reciting these words, he pours again one driblet of libation from the libation cup into the mortar with the left hand, and putting the cup back, he pounds the hom (and) pomegranate twigs with the right hand using the pestle. And from cit upto that vāstārǝm, he completes the entire Ahuna Vairiia, until there he rings the mortar. And (after) completing the second Ahuna Vairiia, holding the pestle in the left hand, he holds (it) above the perforated saucer and picking up the mortar with the right hand, he pours one driblet of hom on the lower surface of the pestle in such a way that it drops via the pestle through the perforated saucer into the cup below.

fields.label: Par.10.37.3
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm

fields.label: Par.10.37.3
fields.html: And beginning the third Ahuna Vairiia (yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcit haca). While reciting these words, he pours again one driblet of libation from the libation cup into the mortar with the left hand and putting the cup back, he pounds the hom (and) pomegranate twigs with the right hand using the pestle. And from vaŋhǝ̄uš upto that vāstārǝm, until the entire Ahuna Vairiia is completed, he rings the mortar. And (after) completing the third Ahuna Vairiia, holding the pestle in the left hand, he holds (it) above the perforated saucer and picking up the mortar with the right hand, he pours one driblet of hom on the lower surface of the pestle in such a way that it drops via the pestle through the perforated saucer into the cup below.

fields.label: Par.10.37.4
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm

fields.label: Par.10.37.4
fields.html: And beginning the fourth Ahuna Vairiia (yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcit haca vaŋhǝ̄uš mazdā). While reciting these words, he pours again a driblet of libation from the libation cup into the mortar with the left hand, and putting the cup back, he pounds the hom (and) pomegranate twigs with the right hand using the pestle. And from manaŋhō upto that vāstārǝm, until the entire Ahuna Vairiia is completed, he rings the mortar. And (after) completing the fourth Ahuna Vairiia, taking the pestle in the left hand, he holds (it) above the perforated saucer, and picking up the mortar with the right hand (and) pouring the entire hom on the lower surface of the pestle, he inspects the surface of the pestle. If any residue of hom (or) pomegranate twigs is stuck on it, then he throws it in the perforated saucer with the right hand. And cleaning the pestle, he puts (it) back in the water container. And then he inspects the mortar again. If in it any residue of hom (or) pomegranate twigs is left, then putting that also in the perforated saucer with the right hand, he cleans the mortar. And holding with the right hand the perforated saucer above the hom cup (which is) below it (and) without touching (it), cleaning (it) with the finger, he strains the hom.

fields.label: Par.10.38.1
fields.html: yǝ̄ səuuištō ahurō mazdā̊scā ārmaitišcā ašəmcā frādat.gaēϑəm manascā vohū xšaϑrəmcā sraotā mōi mərəždātā mōi ādāi kahiiāicīt paitī (3×) </br> ādāi kahiiāicīt paitī (2×)

fields.label: Par.10.38.1
fields.html: And rubbing (and) squeezing the hom (and) pomegranate twigs, while removing its juice, he recites three times.

fields.label: Par.10.39.1
fields.html: us mōi uzārəšuuā ahurā ārmaitī təuuīšīm dasuuā spǝ̄ništā mainiiū mazdā vaŋhuiiā zauuō ādā ašā hazō ǝ̄mauuat vohū manaŋhā fǝsǝratūm

fields.label: Par.10.39.1
fields.html: And he puts the perforated saucer back on the mortar. And the hom (and) pomegranate twigs which are within it, taking them in the right hand, putting (them) separately outside the table in another clean place, he cleans that saucer and its holes. Then putting in it the bull’s hair ring, he takes the libation cup in the left hand. And while rubbing the finger of the right hand on the knot which is tied to the bull’s hair ring, (and) while pouring little by little the libation water from the libation cup on that ring.

fields.label: Par.10.40.1
fields.html: rafəδrāi vourucašānē dōišī mōi yā vǝ̄ abifrā tā xšaϑrahiiā ahurā yā vaŋhǝ̄uš ašiš manaŋhō frō spəntā ārmaitē ašā daēnā̊ fradaxšaiiā

fields.label: Par.10.41.1
fields.html: at rātąm zaraϑuštrō tanuuascīt xᵛaxiiā̊ uštanəm dadāitī pauruuatātəm manaŋhascā vaŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi šiiaoϑanahiiā ašāi yācā uxδaxiiācā səraošəm xšaϑrəmcā

fields.label: Par.10.41.2
fields.html: While reciting until there, finishing all the water within that libation cup, puts (it) back at its place. And he recites ašǝm once again in a low tone. And taking in the left hand the hom cup near the base of the moon-shaped stands, holding in the right hand the perforated saucer along with the bull’s hair ring, while reciting humata three times in a low tone as detailed below, he pours some hom from the cup in the perforated saucer such that it falls towards the right hand side on the table. Then he holds the perforated saucer upon that libation cup which has been emptied. And while reciting hūxta in a low tone, he pours some hom from the cup into the perforated saucer in such a way that it falls only in that libation cup. Then he holds again the perforated saucer upon the mortar, and while reciting huuaršta in a low tone, he pours some hom from the cup into the perforated saucer in such a way that it falls only in that mortar. But in the final time, pouring that entire hom water into the mortar, he puts back the empty cup at its place near the base of the moon-shaped stands.

fields.label: Par.10.41.3
fields.html: And putting back the perforated saucer along with the ring of bull’s hair on that cup, taking the mortar with the right hand, he pours all the water from it into the perforated saucer and he puts the mortar at its place at the edge of the table towards the fire. He puts the ring of bull’s hair at its place in the cup. Then removing the hom cup from the top of that libation cup, he puts (it) near the libation cup closer to him, and putting the milk saucer at its place near the base of the moon-shaped stands, he puts the libation wire on it. The hom (and) pomegranate twigs which have been kept on the base of the moon-shaped stands, from that, taking three pieces of hom twigs and one piece of pomegranate twig, he puts (them) at their place in the saucer. Taking some more of the hom (and) pomegranate twigs, he puts them in the hom cup (which is) meant for covering, near the moon-shaped stands on his left hand side. And pouring a driblet of hom in it from the hom cup near the base of the moon-shaped stands, he covers (it). And putting the remaining hom (and) pomegranate twigs in the cup near the base of the moon-shaped stands (and) putting the left hand on the bundle, he sits.

fields.label: Par.10.42.1
fields.html: yaϑā ahū vairiiō aϑā ratuš ašātcīt hacā vaŋhǝ̄uš dazdā manaŋhō šiiaoϑǝnanąm aŋhǝ̄uš mazdāi xšaϑrǝmcā ahurāi ā yim drigubiiō dadat vāstarǝm (2×)

fields.label: Par.10.42.1
fields.html: After that, that hom strainer priest, lifting the hand from the bundle, taking the libation wire in the left hand and the bull’s hair ring in the right hand, he releases the bāj of the bull’s hair.

fields.label: Par.10.42.2
fields.html: yasnǝmca vahmǝmca aojasca zauuarǝca āfrīnāmi zaraϑuštrahe spitāmahe ašaonō frauuašǝ̄e

fields.label: Par.10.42.2
fields.html: Reciting this much, dipping the bull’s hair ring in the libation cup, he puts (it) at its place in the cup and he puts back the libation wire on the milk saucer. If he does the Yasna or the Vidēvdād of Mīno Nāvar, Gāthā, Ardāfravaš or Sīrojā, or he does the Yasna for the dedication to every vīśpeśām, then he keeps that bull’s hair open. And (if) he does the Yasna or Vidēvdād of Sraoša, Dādār Ahura Mazdā, or any other divinity, then he covers the cup of bull’s hair with another saucer. And the hom strainer priest, taking in the right hand that uncovered hom cup (which is) near the base of the moon-shaped stands, getting up, puts (it) in the stone niche. And bringing the milk jug, he pours (it) in the saucer by taking care that the water droplets on it (= jug) do not splash on the other implements. Then bringing the consecrated bread with clean hands, he puts (it) in the plate on the table. And if the wood (and) incense have not been put on the fire, then putting it.

fields.label: Par.10.42.3
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm

fields.label: Par.10.42.3
fields.html: Coming outside in another pāvī, he recites.

fields.label: Y.0.0.1
fields.html: After that, the priest who is about to become the chief priest, he standing in the pāvī outside of the pāvī of the table of the ritual precinct, reciting one Ašǝm Vohū.

fields.label: Y.0.0.2
fields.html:
(The chief priest), coming into the pāvī of the table, stands near the water container containing the pure implements.
And if the Yasna of Mīno Nāwar or any of the days is to be performed, then he recites seven Ahuna Vairiia.

fields.label: Y.0.0.3
fields.html: Then, the chief priest taking the jug which has been made pure, in his right hand, while reciting, he makes his left hand pure and inserting that hand, which has been made pure, into the jug, he holds the jug.

xšnaoϑra ahurahe mazdā̊

fields.html: In this way, after having made both hands pure, the chief priest facing the East (standing) in front of the fire urn, recites.

fields.label: Y.0.1.1
fields.html: The bundle is of twenty-one twigs and two frāgām(-twigs). Bind the bundle, prepare the parāhōm and place all implements. Who wants to act as chief priest, say one ašəm vohū(-prayer), clean his hands with ritual ablution, go to the place of the fire-tending (priest), face the fire and say three ašəm vohū(-prayers).

fields.label: Y.3.1.1
fields.html: The assistant priest puts the consecrated bread with the ghee on the table and sets three (pieces of) wood (and) incense on the stone near the fire urn. The chief priest inspects the Paragnā (set up) and taking water from the water container, pours (it) on the bundle. Both (priests) recite.

fields.label: Y.3.1.1
fields.html: The bread and the ghee and three pieces of firewood and incense are to be put down. There is no need for the unmarked bread. At the beginning of the Srōš Drōn, with any time to spare everything is to be gazed at. Until the (time of) partaking of the Srōš Drōn, the bull’s hair and the implements are to be kept away from the bundle. When they do come into contact it is permissible. Put in place at least three twigs of hōm and one of pomegranate.

fields.label: Y.11.11.1
fields.html: The partaker (of the parahōm) is to say 3 ašǝm vohū (-prayers).

fields.label: Y.11.11.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.11.11.2
fields.html:
The chief priest taking care that the left hand does not touch the mouth sheet (and) become impure, after lifting the mouth sheet with the left hand, drinks one third part of the hom inside the cup and gazes towards the assistant priest. The assistant priest, standing on the Western side, while putting fragrant incense on the fire, recites alone (1 ašǝm vohū -prayer).
The chief priest, lifting the mouth sheet with care, drinks half part of the remaining hom, and gazes towards the assistant priest. The assistant priest, for the second time, looking at the bundle, while putting the fragrant incense on the fire, recites alone (1 ašǝm vohū -prayer).
The chief priest, lifting the mouth sheet with care, drinks the entire remaining hom and gazes towards the assistant priest and the assistant priest, for the third time, while offering the fragrant incense on the fire, recites (1 ašǝm vohū -prayer).
The chief priest washing (and) making pure that hom cup three times, filling (it) with water, puts it back at its place. Then, cleaning his own mouth, wipes (it). Making the right hand pure again, he puts (it) on the cup and puts the left hand on the bundle.

fields.label: Y.11.11.2
fields.html: (The partaker of the parahōm) is to drink the parahōm in three (sips), each time (he sips), the assistant priest is to say 2 ašǝm vohū (-prayers), the chief priest is to clean his mouth, to ritually wash both hands, to place his left hand on the bundle.

fields.label: Y.11.12.1
fields.html: The chief priest, taking that hom cup in the hand, releases the bāj alone. While reciting the first of the four Ašǝm Vohū, he pours one driblet of water on the place of that cup itself; while reciting the second, he pours one driblet near the base of the moon-shaped stand near to him; while reciting the third, he pours (the water) near the base of the moon-shaped stand towards the fire; and while reciting the fourth, he pours all the water from that cup near the cup with the bull’s hair (ring). Then he inverts that cup, (held) in the hand, near the milk saucer, (which is) near the moon-shaped stand towards the fire plate. The assistant priest sets two (pieces of) wood (and) incense on the two stones.

fields.label: Y.15.1.1
fields.html: The chief priest and the assistant priest both say sastica and the chief priest, while saying sastica, after taking the date-palm leaf on which the knot has been tied first, he fixes (it) on the right horn of the moon-shaped stand. And while saying vantāca, after striking that inverted cup (which is) near the base of the moon-shaped stands, he turns (it) upright. Then the chief priest recites alone.

fields.label: Y.15.1.1
fields.html: The chief priest and the assistant priest should say both sastica, incense is to be given to the fire. Five barsom(-twigs) are to be counted (from the bundle) according to the two criteria (of straighteness and strength); one twig, which is straightest (and the strongest), make it stick out (from the bundle) to serve as datuš(-twig). And thus, loosen the knot properly, the bundle is to be tied to the moon-shaped stand. He should put (his) hand on the bundle.

fields.label: Y.15.2.1

fields.label: Y.15.2.1
fields.html: The chief priest and the assistant priest say yeŋhē mē together. And the chief priest while saying yeŋhē mē, taking the milk saucer, pours some milk in the cup near the base of the moon-shaped stands and while saying ašāt hacā, he pours two parts of milk from the cup into the saucer. Then, from vahištǝm yesnē paitī, the chief priest takes in the right hand the libation wire, which (is) on the milk saucer, wets (it) in the milk saucer (and) goes on touching it to the date-palm leaf of the bundle, upto the word ustǝmǝmcīt.

fields.label: Y.15.2.1

The chief priest, taking the wire in the hand, putting together the knees of both legs, putting the big toe of the right leg on top of the big toe of the left leg, while wetting the date-palm leaf of the bundle, recites the 4 Ahuna Vairiia.
And the assistant priest putting 4 (pieces of) wood (and) incense on the ladle, while reciting the 4 Ahuna Vairiia and 3 Ašǝm Vohū, he puts (the wood and incense) on the fire.

adā tašā gǝ̄uš pərəsat ašəm kaϑā tōi gauuōi ratuš
hiiat hīm dātā xšaiiantō hadā vāstrā gaodāiiō ϑβaxšō
kə̄m hōi uštā ahurəm yə̄ drəguuōdəbīš aēšəməm vādāiiōit

fields.html:
ahmāi ašā nōit sarəjā aduuaēšō gauuōi paitī.mrauuat
auuaēšąm nōit vīduiiē yā šauuaitē ādrǝ̄ng ərəšuuā̊ŋhō
hātąm huuō aojištō yahmāi zauuǝ̄ng jimā kərədušā

mazdā̊ saxᵛārə̄ mairištō yā zī vāuuərəzōi pairī.ciϑīt

at ə̄ vaocat ahurō mazdā̊ vīduuā̊ vafūš viiānaiiā

at zī ϑβā fšuiiantaēcā vāstriiāicā ϑβōrəštā tatašā

tǝ̄m āzūtōiš ahurō mąϑrəm tašat ašā hazaošō

kastē vohū manaŋhā yə̄ ī dāiiāt ǝ̄əāuuā marətaēibiiō

aēm mōi idā vistō yə̄ nə̄ aēuuō sāsnā̊ gūšatā

carəkərəϑrā srāuuaiieŋhē hiiat hōi hudəmə̄m diiāi vaxəδrahiiā

atcā gǝ̄uš uruuā raostā yə̄ anaēšəm xšąnmə̄nē rādəm

kadā yauuā huuō aŋhat yə̄ hōi dadat zastauuat auuō

yūžə̄m aēibiiō ahurā aogō dātā ašā xšaϑrəmcā
auuat vohū manaŋhā yā hušǝ̄itīš rāmąmcā dāt
azə̄mcīt ahiiā mazdā ϑβąm mə̄ŋhī paouruuīm vaēdəm

ahiiā yāsā nəmaŋhā ustānazastō rafəδrahiiā

xšmāuuiia.gǝ̄uš.uruuąm hāitīm yazamaide

fields.label: Y.30.1.1
fields.html:
at tā vaxšiiā išəntō yā mazdāϑā hiiatcīt vīdušē
staotācā ahurāi yesniiācā vaŋhǝ̄uš manaŋhō

fields.html: The chief priest, putting the wire (back), recites alone.

fields.label: Y.30.2.1

sraotā gǝ̄ušāiš vahištā auuaēnatā sūcā manaŋhā
āuuarənā̊ vīciϑahiiā narǝ̄m narəm xᵛaxiiāi tanuiiē
parā mazə̄ yā̊ŋhō ahmāi nə̄ sazdiiāi baodantō paitī

at tā mainiiū pauruiiē yā yǝ̄mā xᵛafənā asruuātəm
manahicā vacahicā šiiaoϑanōi hī vahiiō akəmcā
ā̊scā hudā̊ŋhō ərəš vīšiiātā nōit duždā̊ŋhō

fields.html:
atcā hiiat tā hə̄m mainiiū jasaētəm

fields.html:
aiiā̊ maniuuā̊ varatā yə̄ drəguuā̊ acištā vərəziiō

fields.html:
aiiā̊ nōit ərəš vīšiiātā daēuuācinā hiiat īš ā.dəbaomā

ahmāicā xšaϑrā jasat manaŋhā vohū ašācā

atcā yadā aēšąm kaēnā jamaitī aēnaŋhąm

atcā tōi vaēm xiiāmā yōi īm fərašə̄m kərənaon ahūm

adā zī auuā drūjō auuō bauuaitī skəndō spaiiaϑrahiiā

tā və̄ uruuātā marəntō aguštā vacā̊ sǝ̄nghāmahī

yezī āiš nōit uruuānē aduuā̊ aibī.dərəštā vaxiiā̊

ahmāi aŋhat vahištəm yə̄ mōi vīduuā̊ vaocāt haiϑīm

aϑrā vācəm baraitī miϑahuuacā̊ vā ərəšuuacā̊ vā

axiiācā xᵛaētuš yāsat ahiiā vərəzə̄nəm mat airiiamnā

fields.label: Y.33.11.1
fields.html: The chief priest and the assistant recite aloud. And the chief priest, while reciting yǝ̄ sǝuuištō pours the pounded hom and the pomegranate twigs from the mortar entirely into the perforated saucer and he puts the mortar upright back to its place. Then pouring the libation water from the libation cup into the mortar, he puts that cup inverted to its place. Then, he pours again the libation water from the mortar into the perforated saucer and after cleaning the mortar, he inverts (it). Then holding in the hand the perforated saucer, cleaning with the finger, he strains the hom and after squeezing the hom (and) the pomegranate twigs, while removing the juice, he completes the stanza of yǝ̄ sǝuuištō, and taking out the hom (and) the pomegranate twigs, puts (them) in a clean place.

fields.label: Y.33.12.1
fields.html: While reciting the stanza of us mōi uzārǝšuuā, the chief priest, cleaning the perforated saucer, puts (it) on the mortar which has been kept inverted and on it he puts upright the libation cup which was lying inverted, and after taking the hom cup near the base of the moon-shaped stands, he pours in that libation cup. And cleaning the hom cup held in the hand, filling (it) from the water container, he inverts (it) again near the base of the moon-shaped stands, and both recite.

fields.label: Y.34.4.1
fields.html: The assistant priest, coming near the water container, makes his left hand pure, and the chief priest gives in the assistant priest’s left hand the perforated saucer along with the libation cup on it, (which are) on the mortar. The assistant priest, after taking that, going near the fire, taking (a piece of) wood (and) incense on the ladle with the right hand from the top of the stone, puts (them) on the fire. Then, while both recite the stanza of at tōi ātarǝ̄m together, the assistant priest, after going around the fire, (and) coming on the left side of the chief priest, after touching the bundle with that cup, gives (it) in the hand of the chief priest. The chief priest puts that cup on the mortar and puts the milk saucer on it and puts the perforated saucer into the water container.

fields.label: Y.44.1.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
nəmaŋhō ā yaϑā nəmə̄ xšmāuuatō
mazdā friiāi ϑβāuuąs saxiiāt mauuaitē
at nə̄ ašā friiā dazdiiāi hākurənā
yaϑā nə̄ ā vohū jimat manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.44.2.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā aŋhǝ̄uš vahištahiiā paouruuīm
kāϑē sūidiiāi yə̄ ī paitišāt
huuō zī ašā spəntō irixtəm vīspōibiiō
hārō mainiiū ahūmbiš uruuaϑō mazdā

fields.label: Y.44.3.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kasnā ząϑā patā ašahiiā paouruiiō
kasnā xᵛǝ̄ng starǝ̄mcā dāt aduuānəm
kə̄ yā mā̊ uxšiieitī nərəfsaitī ϑβat
tācīt mazdā vasəmī aniiācā vīduiiē

fields.label: Y.44.4.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kasnā dərətā ząmcā adə̄ nabā̊scā
auuapastōiš kə̄ apō uruuarā̊scā
kə̄ vātāi duuąnmaibiiascā yaogət āsū
kasnā vaŋhǝ̄uš mazdā dąmiš manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.44.5.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kə̄ huuāpā̊ raocā̊scā dāt təmā̊scā
kə̄ huuāpā̊ xᵛafnəmcā dāt zaēmācā
kə̄ yā ušā̊ arǝ̄m.piϑβā xšapācā
yā̊ manaoϑrīš cazdōnghuuantəm arəϑahiiā

fields.label: Y.44.6.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
yā frauuaxšiiā yezī tā aϑā haiϑiiā
ašəm šiiaoϑanāiš dəbązaitī ārmaitiš
taibiiō xšaϑrəm vohū cinas manaŋhā
kaēibiiō azīm rāniiō.skərətīm gąm tašō

fields.label: Y.44.7.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kə̄ bərəxδąm tāšt xšaϑrā mat ārmaitīm
kə̄ uzəmə̄m cōrət viiānaiiā puϑrəm piϑrē
azə̄m tāiš ϑβā fraxšnī auuāmī mazdā
spəntā mainiiū vīspanąm dātārəm

fields.label: Y.44.8.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
məndaidiiāi yā tōi mazdā ādištiš
yācā vohū uxδā frašī manaŋhā
yācā ašā aŋhǝ̄uš arǝ̄m vaēdiiāi
kā mə̄ uruuā vohū uruuāšat āgəmat tā

fields.label: Y.44.9.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā mōi yąm yaoš daēnąm yaoš dānē
yąm hudānāuš paitišə saxiiāt xšaϑrahiiā
ərəšuuā xšaϑrā ϑβāuuąs asīštīš mazdā
hadəmōi ašā vohucā šiiąs manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.44.10.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
tąm daēnąm yā hātąm vahištā
yā mōi gaēϑā̊ ašā frādōit hacə̄mnā
ārmatōiš uxδāiš šiiaoϑanā ərəš daidiiat
maxiiā̊ cistōiš ϑβā īštīš usə̄n mazdā

fields.label: Y.44.11.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā tǝ̄ng ā vījə̄miiāt ārmaitiš
yaēibiiō mazdā ϑβōi vašiietē daēnā
azə̄m tōi āiš paouruiiō frauuōiuuīdē
vīspǝ̄ng aniiǝ̄ng mainiiǝ̄uš spasiiā duuaēšaŋhā

fields.label: Y.44.12.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kə̄ ašauuā yāiš pərəsāi drəguuā̊ vā
katārǝ̄m ā angrō vā huuō vā angrō
yə̄ mā drəguuā̊ ϑβā sauuā paitī.ərətē
ciiaŋhat huuō nōit aiiǝ̄m angrō maniietē

fields.label: Y.44.13.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā drujəm nīš ahmat ā nīš nāšāmā
tǝ̄ng ā auuā yōi asruštōiš pərənā̊ŋhō
nōit ašahiiā ādīuuiieintī hacə̄mnā
nōit frasaiiā vaŋhǝ̄uš cāxnarə̄ manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.44.14.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā ašāi drujə̄m diiąm zastaiiō
nī hīm mərąždiiāi ϑβahiiā mąϑrāiš sǝ̄nghahiiā
ǝ̄mauuaitīm sinąm dāuuōi drəguuasū
ā īš duuafšǝ̄ng mazdā anāšē ąstąscā

fields.label: Y.44.15.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
yezī ahiiā ašā pōi mat xšaiiehī
hiiat hə̄m spādā anaocaŋhā jamaētē
auuāiš uruuātāiš yā tū mazdā dīdərəžō
kuϑrā aiiā̊ kahmāi vananąm dadā̊

fields.label: Y.44.16.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kə̄ vərəϑrəm.jā ϑβā pōi sǝ̄nghā yōi həntī
ciϑrā mōi dąm ahūmbiš ratūm cīždī
at hōi vohū səraošō jantū manaŋhā
mazdā ahmāi yahmāi vašī kahmāicīt

fields.label: Y.44.17.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā mazdā zarəm carānī hacā xšmat
āskətīm xšmākąm hiiatcā mōi xiiāt vāxš aēšō
sarōi būždiiāi hauruuātā amərətātā
auuā mąϑrā yə̄ rāϑəmō ašāt hacā

fields.label: Y.44.18.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
kaϑā ašā tat mīždəm hanānī
dasā aspā̊ aršnauuaitīš uštrəmcā
hiiat mōi mazdā apiuuaitī hauruuātā
amərətātā yaϑā hī taēibiiō dā̊ŋhā

fields.label: Y.44.19.1
fields.html:
tat ϑβā pərəsā ərəš mōi vaocā ahurā
yastat mīždəm hanəntē nōit dāitī
yə̄ īt ahmāi ərəžuxδā nā dāitē
kā tǝ̄m ahiiā mainiš aŋhat paouruiiē
vīduuā̊ auuąm yā īm aŋhat apə̄mā

fields.label: Y.44.20.1
fields.html:
ciϑənā mazdā huxšaϑrā daēuuā ā̊ŋharə̄
at īt pərəsā yōi pišiieintī aēibiiō kąm
yāiš gąm karapā usixšcā aēšəmāi dātā
yācā kauuā ąnmə̄nī urūdōiiatā
nōit hīm mīzə̄n ašā vāstrəm frādaŋhē

fields.label: Y.44.21.1
fields.html:
uštā ahmāi yahmāi uštā kahmāicīt
vasǝ̄ xšaiiąs mazdā̊ dāiiāt ahurō
utaiiūitī təuuīšīm gat tōi vasəmī
ašəm dərədiiāi tat mōi dā̊ ārmaitē
rāiiō ašīš vaŋhǝ̄uš gaēm manaŋhō (2×)

fields.label: Y.45.1.1
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiā nū gūšōdūm nū sraotā
yaēcā asnāt yaēcā dūrāt išaϑā
nū īm vīspā ciϑrē zī mazdā̊ŋhō.dūm
nōit daibitīm duš.sastiš ahūm mərąšiiāt
akā varanā drəguuā̊ hizuuā̊ āuuərətō

fields.label: Y.45.2.1
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiā aŋhǝ̄uš mainiiū paouruiiē
yaiiā̊ spaniiā̊ ūitī mrauuat yǝ̄m angrəm
nōit nā manā̊ nōit sǝ̄nghā nōit xratauuō
naēdā varanā nōit uxδā naēdā šiiaoϑanā
nōit daēnā̊ nōit uruuąnō hacaintē

fields.label: Y.45.3.1
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiā aŋhǝ̄uš ahiiā [paouruuīm
yąm mōi vīduuā̊ mazdā̊ vaocat ahurō
yōi īm və̄ nōit iϑā mąϑrəm varəšəntī
yaϑā īm mə̄nāicā vaocacā
aēibiiō aŋhǝ̄uš auuōi aŋhat apə̄məm]

fields.label: Y.45.4.1
fields.html:
[at frauuaxšiiā aŋhǝ̄uš ahiiā] vahištəm
ašāt hacā mazdā vaēdā yə̄ īm dāt
patarǝ̄m vaŋhǝ̄uš varəzaiiantō manaŋhō
at hōi dugədā hušiiaoϑanā ārmaitiš
nōit diβžaidiiāi vīspā.hišas ahurō

fields.label: Y.45.5.1
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiā hiiat mōi mraot spəntōtəmō
vacə̄ srūidiiāi hiiat marətaēibiiō vahištəm
yōi mōi ahmāi səraošəm dąn caiiascā
upā.jimən hauruuātā amərətātā
vaŋhǝ̄uš mainiiǝ̄uš šiiaoϑanāiš mazdā̊ ahurō

fields.label: Y.45.6.1
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiā vīspanąm mazištəm
stauuas ašā yə̄ hudā̊ yōi həntī
spəntā mainiiū sraotū mazdā̊ ahurō
yehiiā vahmē vohū frašī manaŋhā
ahiiā xratū frō mā sāstū vahištā

fields.label: Y.45.7.1
fields.html:
yehiiā sauuā išā̊ntī rādaŋhō
yōi zī juuā ā̊ŋharəcā buuanticā
amərətāitī ašāunō uruuā aēšō
utaiiūtā yā nərąš sādrā drəguuatō
tācā xšaϑrā mazdā̊ dąmiš ahurō

fields.label: Y.45.8.1
fields.html:
tǝ̄m nə̄ staotāiš nəmaŋhō ā vīuuarəšō
nū zīt cašmainī viiādarəsəm
vaŋhǝ̄uš mainiiǝ̄uš šiiaoϑanahiiā uxδaxiiācā
vīduš ašā yǝ̄m mazdąm ahurəm
at hōi vahmǝ̄ng dəmānē garō nidāmā

fields.label: Y.45.9.1
fields.html:
tǝ̄m nə̄ vohū mat manaŋhā cixšnušō
yə̄ nə̄ usə̄n cōrət spə̄ncā aspə̄ncā
mazdā̊ xšaϑrā vərəzə̄niiā̊ diiāt ahurō
pasūš vīrǝ̄ng ahmākǝ̄ng fradaϑāi ā
vaŋhǝ̄uš ašā haoząϑβāt ā manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.45.10.1
fields.html:
tǝ̄m nə̄ yasnāiš ārmatōiš mimaγžō
yə̄ ąnmə̄nī mazdā̊ srāuuī ahurō
hiiat hōi ašā vohucā cōišt manaŋhā
xšaϑrōi hōi hauruuātā amərətātā
ahmāi stōi dąn təuuīšī utaiiūitī

fields.label: Y.45.11.1
fields.html:
yastā daēuuǝ̄ng aparō mašiiąscā
tarə̄.mąstā yōi īm tarə̄.maniiantā
aniiǝ̄ng ahmāt yə̄ hōi arǝ̄m maniiātā
saošiiantō dǝ̄ng patōiš spəntā daēnā
uruuaϑō barātā patā vā mazdā ahurā

fields.label: Y.45.12.1
fields.html:
uštā ahmāi yahmāi uštā kahmāicīt
vasǝ̄ xšaiiąs mazdā̊ dāiiāt ahurō
utaiiūitī təuuīšīm gat tōi vasəmī
ašəm dərədiiāi tat mōi dā̊ ārmaitē
rāiiō ašīš vaŋhǝ̄uš gaēm manaŋhō (2×)

fields.label: Y.45.12.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite, the chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.45.12.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.45.12.2
fields.html: The chief priest puts the wire (back).

fields.label: Y.45.12.3
fields.html:
at frauuaxšiiąm hāitīm yazamaide
yeŋhē hātąm āat yesnē paitī vaŋhō mazdā̊ ahurō vaēϑā ašāt hacā yā̊ŋhąmcā tąscā tā̊scā yazamaide

fields.label: Y.46.1.1
fields.html:
kąm nəmōi ząm kuϑrā nəmōi aiienī
pairī xᵛaētǝ̄uš airiiamanascā dadaitī
nōit mā xšnāuš yā vərəzə̄nā hǝ̄cā
naēdā daxiiǝ̄uš yōi sāstārō drəguuantō
kaϑā ϑβā mazdā xšnaošāi ahurā

fields.label: Y.46.2.1
fields.html:
vaēdā tat yā ahmī mazdā anaēšō
mā kamnafšuuā hiiatcā kamnānā ahmī
gərəzōi tōi ā īt auuaēnā ahurā
rafəδrǝ̄m caguuā̊ hiiat friiō friiāi daidīt
āxsō vaŋhǝ̄uš ašā īštīm manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.46.3.1
fields.html:
kadā mazdā yōi uxšānō asnąm
aŋhǝ̄uš darəϑrāi frō ašahiiā frārəntē
vərəzdāiš sǝ̄nghāiš saošiiantąm xratauuō
kaēibiiō ūϑāi vohū jimat manaŋhā
maibiiō ϑβā sąstrāi vərənē ahurā

fields.label: Y.46.4.1
fields.html:
at tǝ̄ng drəguuā̊ yǝ̄ng ašahiiā važdrǝ̄ng pāt
gā̊ frōrətōiš šōiϑrahiiā vā daxiiǝ̄uš vā
dužazōbā̊ hąs xᵛāiš šiiaoϑanāiš ahə̄mustō
yastǝ̄m xšaϑrāt mazdā mōiϑat jiiātǝ̄uš vā
huuō tǝ̄ng frō.gā̊ paϑmǝ̄ng hucistōiš carāt

fields.label: Y.46.5.1
fields.html:
yə̄ vā xšaiiąs adąs drītā aiiantəm
uruuātōiš vā huzə̄ntuš miϑrōibiiō vā
rašnā juuąs yə̄ ašauuā drəguuantəm
vīcirō hąs tat frō xᵛaētauuē mruiiāt
uzūiϑiiōi īm mazdā xrūniiāt ahurā

fields.label: Y.46.6.1
fields.html:
at yastǝ̄m nōit nā isəmnō āiiāt
drūjō huuō dāmąn haēϑahiiā gāt
huuō zī drəguuā̊ yə̄ drəguuāitē vahištō
huuō ašauuā yahmāi ašauuā friiō
hiiat daēnā̊ paouruiiā̊ dā̊ ahurā

fields.label: Y.46.7.1
fields.html:
kə̄m.nā mazdā mauuaitē pāiiūm dadāt
hiiat mā drəguuā̊ dīdarəšatā [aēnaŋhē
aniiǝ̄m ϑβahmāt āϑrascā manaŋhascā
yaiiā̊ šiiaoϑanāiš ašəm ϑraoštā ahurā
tąm mōi dąstuuąm daēnaiiāi frāuuaocā]

fields.label: Y.46.8.1
fields.html:
[yə̄ vā mōi yā̊ gaēϑā̊ dazdē aēnaŋhē
nōit ahiiā mā āϑriš šiiaoϑanāiš frōsiiāt
paitiiaogət tā ahmāi jasōit duuaēšaŋhā]
tanuuə̄m ā yā īm hujiiātōiš pāiiāt
nōit dužjiiātōiš kācīt [mazdā duuaēšaŋhā]

fields.label: Y.46.9.1
fields.html:
kə̄ huuō yə̄ mā arədrō cōiϑat paouruiiō
yaϑā ϑβā zəuuīštīm uzəmōhī
šiiaoϑanōi spəntəm [ahurəm ašauuanəm
yā tōi ašā yā ašāi gǝ̄uš tašā mraot]
išəntī mā tā tōi [vohū manaŋhā]

fields.label: Y.46.10.1
fields.html:
yə̄ vā mōi nā gənā vā mazdā ahurā
dāiiāt aŋhǝ̄uš yā tū vōistā vahištā
ašīm ašāi vohū xšaϑrəm manaŋhā
yąscā haxšāi xšmāuuatąm vahmāi ā
frō.tāiš vīspāiš cinuuatō frafrā pərətūm

fields.label: Y.46.11.1
fields.html:
xšaϑrāiš yūjə̄n karapanō kāuuaiiascā
akāiš šiiaoϑanāiš ahūm mərəngəidiiāi mašīm
yǝ̄ng xᵛə̄ uruuā xᵛaēcā xraodat daēnā
hiiat aibī.gəmən yaϑrā cinuuatō pərətuš
yauuōi vīspāi drūjō dəmānāi astaiiō

fields.label: Y.46.12.1
fields.html:
hiiat us ašā naptiiaēšū nafšucā
tūrahiiā uzjə̄n friiānahiiā aojiiaēšū
ārmatōiš gaēϑā̊ frādō ϑβaxšaŋhā
at īš vohū hə̄m aibī.mōist manaŋhā
aēibiiō rafəδrāi mazdā̊ sastē ahurō

fields.label: Y.46.13.1
fields.html:
yə̄ spitāməm zaraϑuštrəm rādaŋhā
marətaēšū xšnāuš huuō nā fərasrūidiiāi ərəδβō
at hōi mazdā̊ ahūm dadāt ahurō
ahmāi gaēϑā̊ vohū frādat manaŋhā
tǝ̄m və̄ ašā mǝ̄hmaidī hušhaxāim

fields.label: Y.46.14.1
fields.html:
zaraϑuštrā kastē ašauuā uruuaϑō
mazōi magāi kə̄ vā fərasrūidiiāi vaštī
at huuō kauuā vīštāspō yāhī
yǝ̄ngstū mazdā hadəmōi minaš ahurā
tǝ̄ng zbaiiā vaŋhǝ̄uš uxδāiš manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.46.15.1
fields.html:
haēcat.aspā vaxšiiā və̄ spitamā̊ŋhō
hiiat dāϑǝ̄ng vīcaiiaϑā adāϑąscā
tāiš yūš šiiaoϑanāiš ašəm [xšmaibiiā daduiiē
yāiš dātāiš paouruiiāiš ahurahiiā]

fields.label: Y.46.16.1
fields.html:
fərašaoštrā aϑrā tū arədrāiš idī
huuō.guuā tāiš yǝ̄ng usuuahī uštā.stōi
yaϑrā ašā hacaitē ārmaitiš
yaϑrā [vaŋhǝ̄uš manaŋhō īštā xšaϑrəm
yaϑrā mazdā̊ varədəmąm šaēitī ahurō]

fields.label: Y.46.17.1
fields.html:
yaϑrā və̄ afšmānī sǝ̄nghānī
nōit anafšmąm də̄jāmāspā huuō.guuā
hadā və̄stā vahmǝ̄ng səraošā rādaŋhō
yə̄ vīcinaot dāϑəmcā adāϑəmcā
dangrā mantū ašā mazdā̊ ahurō

fields.label: Y.46.18.1
fields.html:
yə̄ maibiiā yaoš ahmāi ascīt vahištā
maxiiā̊ ištōiš vohū cōišəm manaŋhā
ąstǝ̄ng ahmāi yə̄ nā̊ ąstāi daidītā
mazdā ašā xšmākəm vārəm xšnaošəmnō
tat mōi xratǝ̄uš manaŋhascā vīciϑəm

fields.label: Y.46.19.1
fields.html:
yə̄ mōi ašāt haiϑīm hacā varəšaitī
zaraϑuštrāi hiiat vasnā fərašōtəməm
ahmāi mīždəm hanəntē parāhūm
manə̄.vistāiš mat vīspāiš gāuuā azī
tācīt mōi sąs tuuə̄m mazdā vaēdištō

fields.label: Y.46.20.1
fields.html:
uštā ahmāi yahmāi uštā kahmāicīt
vasǝ̄ xšaiiąs mazdā̊ dāiiāt ahurō
utaiiūitī təuuīšīm gat tōi vasəmī
ašəm dərədiiāi tat mōi dā̊ ārmaitē
rāiiō ašīš vaŋhǝ̄uš gaēm manaŋhō (2×)

fields.label: Y.46.20.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite, the chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.46.20.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.46.20.2
fields.html: The chief priest puts the wire (back).

fields.label: Y.46.20.3
fields.html:
kamnamaēząm hāitīm yazamaide uštauuaitīm gāϑąm ašaonīm ašahe ratūm yazamaide uštauuaitiiā̊ gāϑaiiā̊ handātā yazamaide
yeŋhē hātąm āat yesnē paitī vaŋhō mazdā̊ ahurō vaēϑā ašāt hacā yā̊ŋhąmcā tąscā tā̊scā yazamaide

fields.label: Y.47.0.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite.

fields.label: Y.47.1.1
fields.html:
spəntā mainiiū vahištācā manaŋhā
hacā ašāt šiiaoϑanācā vacaŋhācā
ahmāi dąn hauruuātā amərətātā
mazdā̊ xšaϑrā ārmaitī ahurō (2×)

fields.label: Y.47.1.1
fields.html: The chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.47.2.1
fields.html:
ahiiā mainiiǝ̄uš spə̄ništahiiā vahištəm
hizuuā uxδāiš vaŋhǝ̄uš ǝ̄əānū manaŋhō
ārmatōiš zastōibiiā šiiaoϑanā vərəziiat
ōiiā cistī huuō patā ašahiiā mazdā̊

fields.label: Y.47.2.1
fields.html: The chief priest, putting the wire (back), recites alone.

fields.label: Y.47.3.1
fields.html:
ahiiā mainiiǝ̄uš tuuə̄m ahī tā spəntō
yə̄ ahmāi gąm rāniiō.skərətīm hə̄m.tašat
at hōi vāstrāi rāmā.dā̊ ārmaitīm
hiiat hə̄m vohū mazdā hə̄mə.fraštā manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.47.4.1
fields.html:
ahmāt mainiiǝ̄uš rārəšiieintī drəguuantō
mazdā spəntāt nōit iϑā ašāunō
kasǝ̄ušcīt nā ašāunē kāϑə̄ aŋhat
isuuācīt hąs paraoš akō drəguuāitē

fields.label: Y.47.5.1
fields.html:
tācā spəntā mainiiū mazdā ahurā
ašāunē cōiš yā zī cīcā vahištā
hanarə ϑβahmāt zaošāt drəguuā̊ baxšaitī
ahiiā šiiaoϑanāiš akāt [āšiiąs manaŋhō]

fields.label: Y.47.6.1
fields.html:
tā dā̊ spəntā mainiiū mazdā ahurā
āϑrā vaŋhāu vīdāitīm rānōibiiā
ārmatōiš dəbązaŋhā ašaxiiācā
hā zī pourūš išəntō vāurāitē

fields.label: Y.47.7.1
fields.html:
spəntā mainiiū vahištācā manaŋhā
hacā ašāt šiiaoϑanācā vacaŋhācā
ahmāi dąn hauruuātā amərətātā
mazdā̊ xšaϑrā ārmaitī ahurō (2×)

fields.label: Y.47.7.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite, the chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.47.7.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.47.7.2
fields.html: The chief priest puts the wire (back).

fields.label: Y.47.7.3
fields.html:
spəntā.mainiiūm hāitīm yazamaide
yeŋhē hātąm āat yesnē paitī vaŋhō mazdā̊ ahurō vaēϑā ašāt hacā yā̊ŋhąmcā tąscā tā̊scā yazamaide

fields.label: Y.48.1.1
fields.html:
yezī adāiš ašā drujəm və̄nghaitī
hiiat ąsašutā yā daibitānā fraoxtā
amərətāitī daēuuāišcā mašiiāišcā
at tōi sauuāiš vahməm vaxšat ahurā

fields.label: Y.48.2.1
fields.html:
vaocā mōi yā tuuə̄m vīduuā̊ ahurā
[parā hiiat mā yā mǝ̄ng pərəϑā jimaitī
kat ašauuā mazdā vǝ̄nghat drəguuantəm]
hā zī aŋhǝ̄uš vaŋuhī vistā ākərətiš

fields.label: Y.48.3.1
fields.html:
[at vaēdəmnāi vahištā sāsnanąm]
yąm hudā̊ sāstī ašā ahurō
spəntō vīduuā̊ yaēcīt gūzrā sǝ̄nghā̊ŋhō
ϑβāuuąs mazdā vaŋhǝ̄uš xraϑβā manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.48.4.1
fields.html:
yə̄ dāt manō vahiiō mazdā ašiiascā
huuō daēnąm šiiaoϑanācā vacaŋhācā
ahiiā zaošǝ̄ng uštiš varənǝ̄ng hacaitē
ϑβahmī xratā̊ apə̄məm nanā aŋhat

fields.label: Y.48.5.1
fields.html:
huxšaϑrā xšə̄ntąm mā nə̄ dušə.xšaϑrā xšə̄ntā
vaŋhuiiā̊ cistōiš šiiaoϑanāiš ārmaitē
yaoždā̊ mašiiāi aipī ząϑəm vahištā
gauuōi vərəziiātąm tąm nə̄ xᵛarəϑāi fšuiiō

fields.label: Y.48.6.1
fields.html:
hā zī nə̄ hušōiϑəmā hā nə̄ utaiiūitīm
dāt təuuīšīm vaŋhǝ̄uš manaŋhō bərəxδē
at axiiāi ašā mazdā̊ uruuarā̊ vaxšat
ahurō aŋhǝ̄uš ząϑōi paouruiiehiiā

fields.label: Y.48.7.1
fields.html:
nī aēšəmō nī diiātąm paitī rəməm paitī siiōzdūm
yōi ā vaŋhǝ̄uš manaŋhō dīdraγžōduiiē
ašā viiąm yehiiā hiϑāuš nā spəntō
at hōi dāmąm ϑβahmī ā dąm ahurā

fields.label: Y.48.8.1
fields.html:
kā tōi vaŋhǝ̄uš mazdā xšaϑrahiiā īštiš
kā tōi ašōiš ϑβaxiiā̊ maibiiō ahurā
kā ϑβōi ašā ākā̊ arədrǝ̄ng išiiā
vaŋhǝ̄uš mainiiǝ̄uš šiiaoϑananąm jauuarō

fields.label: Y.48.9.1
fields.html:
kadā vaēdā yezī cahiiā xšaiiaϑā
mazdā ašā yehiiā mā āiϑiš duuaēϑā
ərəš mōi ərəžūcąm vaŋhǝ̄uš vafuš manaŋhō
vīdiiāt saošiiąs yaϑā hōi ašiš aŋhat

fields.label: Y.48.10.1
fields.html:
kadā mazdā mąnarōiš narō vīsəntē
kadā ajə̄n mūϑrəm ahiiā magahiiā
yā angraiiā karapanō urūpaiieintī
yācā xratū dušə.xšaϑrā daxiiunąm

fields.label: Y.48.11.1
fields.html:
kadā mazdā ašā mat ārmaitiš
jimat xšaϑrā hušəitiš vāstrauuaitī
kōi drəguuōdəbīš xrūrāiš rāmąm dā̊ntē
kǝ̄ng ā vaŋhǝ̄uš jimat manaŋhō cistiš

fields.label: Y.48.12.1
fields.html:
[at tōi aŋhən saošiiantō daxiiunąm]
yōi xšnūm vohū manaŋhā hacā̊ntē
šiiaoϑanāiš ašā ϑβahiiā mazdā sǝ̄nghahiiā
tōi zī dātā hamaēstārō aēšəm mahiiā

fields.label: Y.48.13.1
fields.html:
spəntā mainiiū vahištācā manaŋhā
hacā ašāt šiiaoϑanācā vacaŋhācā
ahmāi dąn hauruuātā amərətātā
mazdā̊ xšaϑrā ārmaitī ahurō (2×)

fields.label: Y.48.13.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite, the chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.48.13.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.48.13.2
fields.html: The chief priest puts the wire (back).

fields.label: Y.48.13.3
fields.html:
yeziδąm hāitīm yazamaide
yeŋhē hātąm āat yesnē paitī vaŋhō mazdā̊ ahurō vaēϑā ašāt hacā yā̊ŋhąmcā tąscā tā̊scā yazamaide

fields.label: Y.49.1.1
fields.html:
at mā yauuā bə̄nduuō pafrē mazištō
[yə̄ dušərəϑrīš cixšnušā ašā mazdā]
vaŋuhī ādā gaidī mōi ā mōi arapā
ahiiā vohū aošō vīdā manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.49.2.1
fields.html:
at ahiiā mā bə̄nduuahiiā mānaiieitī
tkaēšō drəguuā̊ daibitā ašāt rārəšō
nōit spəntąm dōrəšt ahmāi stōi ārmaitīm
naēdā vohū mazdā fraštā manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.49.3.1
fields.html:
atcā ahmāi varənāi mazdā nidātəm
ašəm sūidiiāi tkaēšāi rāšaiieŋhē druxš
tā vaŋhǝ̄uš sarə̄ iziiāi manaŋhō
antarə̄ vīspǝ̄ng drəguuatō haxmǝ̄ng antarə̄ mruiiē

fields.label: Y.49.4.1
fields.html:
yōi duš.xraϑβā aēšəməm varədən rāməmcā
xᵛāiš hizubīš fšuiiasū afšuiiantō
yaēšąm nōit huuarštāiš vąs dužuuarštā
tōi daēuuǝ̄ng dąn yā drəguuatō daēnā

fields.label: Y.49.5.1
fields.html:
at huuō mazdā īžācā āzūitišcā
yə̄ daēnąm vohū sārštā manaŋhā
ārmatōiš kascīt ašā huzə̄ntuš
tāišcā vīspāiš ϑβahmī xšaϑrōi ahurā

fields.label: Y.49.6.1
fields.html:
frō vā̊ fraēšiiā mazdā ašəmcā mrūitē
yā və̄ xratǝ̄uš xšmākahiiā ā.manaŋhā
ərəš [vīcidiiāi yaϑā ī srāuuaiiaēmā
tąm daēnąm yā xšmāuuatō ahurā]

fields.label: Y.49.7.1
fields.html:
tatcā vohū mazdā sraotū manaŋhā
sraotū ašā gūšahuuā.tū ahurā
kə̄ airiiamā kə̄ xᵛaētuš dātāiš aŋhat
yə̄ vərəzǝ̄nāi vaŋuhīm dāt frasastīm

fields.label: Y.49.8.1
fields.html:
fərašaoštrāi uruuāzištąm ašahiiā dā̊
sarǝ̄m tat ϑβā mazdā yāsā ahurā
maibiiācā yąm vaŋhāu ϑβahmī ā.xšaϑrōi
yauuōi vīspāi fraēštā̊ŋhō ā̊ŋhāmā

fields.label: Y.49.9.1
fields.html:
sraotū sāsnā̊ fšǝ̄nghiiō suiiē taštō
nōit ərəš.vacā̊ sarǝ̄m didąs drəguuātā
hiiat daēnā̊ vahištē yūjə̄n mīždē
ašā yuxtā yāhī də̄jāmāspā

fields.label: Y.49.10.1
fields.html:
tatcā mazdā ϑβahmī ādąm nipā̊ŋhē
manō vohū urunascā ašāunąm
nəmascā yā ārmaitiš īžācā
mązā xšaϑrā vazdaŋhā auuə̄mīrā

fields.label: Y.49.11.1
fields.html:
at dušəxšaϑrǝ̄ng duš.šiiaoϑanǝ̄ng dužuuacaŋhō
duždaēnǝ̄ng duš.manaŋhō drəguuatō
akāiš xᵛarəϑāiš paitī uruuąnō paitiieintī
drūjō dəmānē haiϑiiā aŋhən astaiiō

fields.label: Y.49.12.1
fields.html:
kat tōi ašā zbaiientē auuaŋhō
zaraϑuštrāi kat tōi vohū manaŋhā
yə̄ və̄ staotāiš mazdā frīnāi ahurā
auuat yāsąs hiiat və̄ īštā vahištəm

fields.label: Y.49.13.1
fields.html:
spəntā mainiiū vahištācā manaŋhā
hacā ašāt šiiaoϑanācā vacaŋhācā
ahmāi dąn hauruuātā amərətātā
mazdā̊ xšaϑrā ārmaitī ahurō (2×)

fields.label: Y.49.13.1
fields.html: The chief priest (and) the assistant priest both recite, the chief priest takes the wire.

fields.label: Y.49.13.2
fields.html: ašəm vohū vahištəm astī uštā astī uštā ahmāi hiiat ašāi vahištāi ašǝm (3×)

fields.label: Y.49.13.2
fields.html: The chief priest puts the wire (back).

fields.label: Y.49.13.3
fields.html:
at māiiauuąm hāitīm yazamaide
yeŋhē hātąm āat yesnē paitī vaŋhō mazdā̊ ahurō vaēϑā ašāt hacā yā̊ŋhąmcā tąscā tā̊scā yazamaide

fields.label: Y.50.1.1
fields.html:
kat mōi uruuā isē cahiiā auuaŋhō
kə̄ mōi pasǝ̄uš kə̄ mə̄.nā ϑrātā vistō
aniiō ašāt ϑβatcā mazdā ahurā
azdā zūtā vahištāatcā manaŋhō

fields.label: Y.50.2.1
fields.html:
kaϑā mazdā rāniiō.skərətīm gąm išasōit
yə̄ hīm ahmāi vāstrauuaitīm stōi usiiāt
ərəžəjīš ašā pourušū xᵛarə̄ pišiiasū
ākāstǝ̄ng mā nišąsiiā dāϑə̄m dāhuuā

fields.label: Y.50.3.1
fields.html:
atcīt ahmāi mazdā ašā aŋhaitī
yąm hōi xšaϑrā vohucā cōišt manaŋhā
yə̄ nā ašōiš aojaŋhā varədaiiaētā
yąm nazdištąm gaēϑąm drəguuā̊ baxšaitī

fields.label: Y.50.4.1
fields.html:
at vā̊ yazāi stauuas mazdā ahurā
hadā ašā vahištācā manaŋhā
xšaϑrācā yā īšō stā̊ŋhat ā.paiϑī
ākā̊ arədrǝ̄ng dəmānē garō səraošānē

fields.label: Y.50.5.1
fields.html:
ārōi zī xšmā mazdā ašā ahurā
hiiat yūšmākāi mąϑrānē vaorāzaϑā
aibī.dərəštā āuuīšiiā auuaŋhā
zastāištā yā nā̊ xᵛāϑrē dāiiāt

fields.label: Y.50.6.1
fields.html:
yə̄ mąϑrā vācəm mazdā baraitī
uruuaϑō ašā nəmaŋhā zaraϑuštrō
dātā xratǝ̄uš hizuuō raiϑīm stōi
mahiiā rāzǝ̄ng vohū sāhīt manaŋhā

fields.label: Y.50.7.1
fields.html:
at və̄ yaojā zəuuīštiiǝ̄ng auruuatō
jaiiāiš pərəϑūš vahmahiiā yūšmākahiiā
mazdā ašā ugrǝ̄ng vohū manaŋhā
yāiš azāϑā mahmāi xiiātā auuaŋhǝ̄

fields.label: Y.50.8.1
fields.html:
mat vā̊ padāiš yā frasrūtā īžaiiā̊
pairijasāi mazdā ustānazastō
at vā̊ ašā arədraxiiācā nəmaŋhā
at vā̊ vaŋhǝ̄uš manaŋhō hunarətātā

fields.label: Y.50.9.1
fields.html:
tāiš vā̊ yasnāiš paitī stauuas aiienī
mazdā ašā vaŋhǝ̄uš šiiaoϑanāiš manaŋhō
yadā ašōiš maxiiā̊ vasə̄ xšaiiā
at hudānāuš išaiiąs gərəzdā xiiǝ̄m

fields.label: Y.50.10.1
fields.html:
at yā varəšā yācā pairī āiš šiiaoϑanā
yācā vohū cašmąm arəjat manaŋhā
raocā̊ xᵛǝ̄ng asnąm uxšā aēuruš

fields.label: Y.65.1.1
fields.html: The chief priest, picking up the cup on the mortar with the left hand, while saying the words yazāi āpəm, he turns the mortar upright with the right hand after striking it three times and while reciting these words arəduuīm sūrąm anāhitąm, he pours some water from the cup in the left hand into the mortar and while saying pərəϑū.frākąm, picking with the right hand the milk saucer, he pours some milk into the mortar and while saying baēšaziiąm, he pours some water from the libation cup, (which is) near the mortar, into the mortar. Then he mixes up the water within both cups into one another, and after holding the cup from above the mortar in the right hand, he puts the second cup on the table. Then the chief priest, getting off from his seat, wearing the sandals, together with the assistant priest (standing) near the moon-shaped stands, while looking straight at the water container completes the prayer to Arǝduuī Sūrā (Anāhitā).

fields.label: Y.68.21.1

fields.label: Y.68.21.1
fields.html:
The chief priest keeps holding the cup along with the bundle in the left hand upon the table, while reciting vaŋuhīm iδāt he touches the Eastern rim of the cup in the left hand with the cup in the right hand; while reciting ādąm vaŋuhīm ašīm he touches the Southern rim (of the cup with it); while reciting āca nica he touches the Western rim (of the cup with it). While reciting mrūmaide, he touches the Northern rim (of the cup with it). While reciting īžā̊ yaoštaiiō apō at yazamaide he pours one driblet into the cup in (his) left hand, while reciting uitī yā vǝ̄ vaŋhǝ̄uš, he pours one driblet from the cup in (his) left hand into the cup in (his) right hand and while reciting apascā vā̊ he pours one driblet from the cup in (his) right hand into the milk saucer.
All the three times he does (it) exactly in that way.

fields.label: Y.68.21.1
fields.html:
At vaŋuhīm ašīm in the way the sun turns, turn the vessel over the brim of that vessel which contains water, at āca over the water, at nica make (it) turn in (the vessel), at mrūmaide he is to fill (it), at īžā̊ he is to turn (it) again in the way the sun turns, at yaoštaiiō he is to hold (it) at four fingers(-height) above the water, at apō place (it) over the water, at at on the way (of that vessel), at yazamaide facing the libation, at ūitī yā və̄ vaŋuhīš (hold it) at the base of the bundle, at four places: on the left and the right and above and below, atapascā facing the libation, at vā̊ pour the water back into the water(-container).
(Recite) three times; do (it) in this manner.

fields.label: Y.72.16.1
fields.html: The assistant priest, (after) going to the well (and) sending away other people from the surroundings of the well, stands in a separate pāvī and the chief priest, going back to his seat, takes the pure jug, (and) makes his left hand pure without reciting anything; (then) taking the mortar (containing) the libation, he comes near the fire, (and) taking fragrant incense on the ladle with the right hand, he puts (it) on the fire, (and then) goes to the well. Then both priests, facing the East, pour the libation. The chief priest, while reciting the Ahuna Vairiia above, pours some libation water from the mortar into the well.
